{
  "texts": [
    "Our 3D shapes showed connectivity, accurate boundary, proper density and good element quality.",
    "As can be seen in the qualitative examples our meshes maintain the same shape as the original ones and can be generated in a very short period of time, even less than a second in most of them.",
    "All results are presented with normalized meshes in a unit sphere.As shown in Table 1, our full set of 53 meshes were processed in a total of 84 s, with an average runtime of approximately 1.22 s per mesh.",
    "This runtime accounts for the entire pipeline, from the misshapen input mesh to its optimized and refined version.",
    "We observed that more complex shapes can take over 5 s in certain cases, particularly when the surface contains numerous edges and irregularities that require higher solver precision."
  ]
}